{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-js","path":"/linux/docker/sqlserver/2017/08/25/sql-server-linux-notes/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Get Docker (if it is not already running) Get the SQL Server on Linux for Docker Engine image I'm running Docker on MacOS, I will use theâ€¦","id":"49e17b3a-0d70-51f6-b13e-4b03f8aa8486","frontmatter":{"title":"SQL Server on Linux via Docker","subtitle":"Reference post for getting SQL Server Linux up and running","excerpt":"Running SQL Server on Linux for Docker Engine","date":"August 25, 2017","author":"Mark Roxberry","featured":true,"tags":["sql server","linux","docker"],"postimage":{"alt":"main post image","src":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/markrox.dev/markrox.dev/temp/src/archive/2017-08-25-sql-server-linux-notes/post.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/c2d17/post.png","srcSet":"/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/76a4f/post.png 750w,\n/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/c2d17/post.png 800w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/2b382/post.avif 750w,\n/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/6ee87/post.avif 800w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/66907/post.webp 750w,\n/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/0d27e/post.webp 800w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.75},"resize":{"src":"/static/53a92f53d91e8401905161ffa2a2a43a/f3583/post.png","height":900,"width":1200}}}}},"html":"<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Get <a href=\"https://www.docker.com/\">Docker</a> (if it is not already running)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Get the SQL Server on Linux for Docker Engine image</p>\n<p>I'm running Docker on MacOS, I will use the SQL Server on Linux for Docker Engine at <a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/r/microsoft/mssql-server-linux/\">Docker Hub</a></p>\n<pre><code>docker pull microsoft/mssql-server-linux\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Set the settings and start the container</p>\n<p>SQL Server on Linux for Docker Engine requires an environment setting to accept the EULA and set a strong SA password:</p>\n<pre><code>ACCEPT_EULA = Y\nSA_PASSWORD = &#x3C;your password>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Run this in the terminal:</p>\n<pre><code>docker run -e 'ACCEPT_EULA=Y' -e 'SA_PASSWORD=yourStrong(!)Password' -p 1433:1433 -d microsoft/mssql-server-linux\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Copy a backup to the container</p>\n<pre><code>docker cp '/tmp/DatabaseName.bak' mssql-server-linux:/tmp\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Restore the backup</p>\n<pre><code>RESTORE DATABASE DatabaseName FROM DISK='/tmp/DatabaseName.bak'\nWITH MOVE 'DatabaseName' TO '/var/opt/mssql/data/DatabaseName.MDF',\nMOVE 'DatabaseName_log' TO '/var/opt/mssql/data/DatabaseName_log.ldf'\nGo\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Connect with a docker command or an IDE like <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/datagrip/\">DataGrip</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/f238d/datagrip.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"DataGrip SQL Server Connection\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/5a190/datagrip.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/772e8/datagrip.png 200w,\n/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/e17e5/datagrip.png 400w,\n/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/5a190/datagrip.png 800w,\n/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/c1b63/datagrip.png 1200w,\n/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/29007/datagrip.png 1600w,\n/static/3b1d4cf66fb65b118e76fe0c5640c766/f238d/datagrip.png 2078w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Using SQL Server for Linux in Docker has allowed me to continue to develop using a Linux distro or macOS without needing to set up a VM to run the database backend.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/linux/docker/sqlserver/2017/08/25/sql-server-linux-notes/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1460613570","2052298874","2446865869","717330468"],"slicesMap":{}}